seit geraumer Zeit in einem besonderen Spannungsfeld zwischen den Anforderungen traditioneller Philologie, moderner Metalexikographie und technischer Innovation. Die Beiträge dieses Sammelbandes spiegeln die damit verbundenen Herausforderungen wie ihre Bewältigung. Sie zeigen, dass die historische Lexikographie konzeptionell wie institutionell durchaus in der Lage ist, sich von Generation zu Generation neu zu erfinden und sich damit den Herausforderungen zu stellen, die die jeweilige Gesellschaft ihnen abverlangt.  aFor some time, historical lexicography has been suspended between the demands of traditional philology, modern metalexicography, and technical innovation. The essays in this compilation volume reflect the challenges associated with these demands as well as ways to overcome them. They also reveal that historical lexicography is conceptually and institutionally capable of continuously re-inventing itself.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGerman languagexLexicographyxHistory. 0aGerman languagexLexicology, Historical. 4aHistorische Sprachwissenschaft. 4aMetalexikographie. 4aWörterbücher. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aDictionaries.  aHistorical linguistics.  aMetalexicography.1 aBär, Jochen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeutsch, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiehl, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHansen, Nils, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarm, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeuser, Rita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlein, Wolf Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voca